

what really happens when we access a website..?

1. URL 
2. DNS 
3. TCP Handshaking 
4. TLS Handshaking
5. HTTP request and response 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------


ctrl + alt + t - open terminal 
ctrl + shift + "+" - to magnify text 



cd:
- change directory 
- used to traverse b/w the directories 

	Eg: cd / 
		cd /home/kali 
		cd /home/kali/downloads 
		
		cd . (. - current directory)
		cd .. (.. - parent directory)
		
		
listing directories:

using ls command:
- listing 
- used to display contents of a folder/directory 

	Eg: ls 
		ls -l 
		ls -a 
		
using dir command:

	Eg: dir 
		dir -l 
		dir -F 
		

Getting Help:
- many commands 
- many options 
- impossible to remember every command every option 
- '-h' or '--help' 
- display short help menu will get displayed 
		
	Eg: rmdir --help 
	
	
man pages:
- manual pages 
- display long description obout the command 

	Eg: man nmap 
		man ls 
		
		
Finding stuff:

using locate command:

- light weight command 
- used to find file 
- it searches for given file in a backend database which updates once in a day
- problem when we search for a newly created file
- "sudo updatedb" to manually update backend database 


	Eg: locate file 
		

whereis:
- used to search for a binary file 
- it also display manual page if available 

	Eg: whereis locate 

which:
- used to search for a binary file but it is even more specific 
- PATH variable 

PATH 
- env variable 
- locations of binaries 

	Eg: echo "$PATH"
	
	Eg: which locate 


find:
- used to search for a file / folder 
- real time used command 
- find do not depend on any database it actually searches on file system 
- find provides multiple options for searching a file 
		- name, size, permissions, date, group,user etc 
		
	Eg: find / -name filename 
		find / -iname Filename 
		find /home/kali -name filename 
		find / -type d -name fol_name 
		find / -type f -perm 0644 
















		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		